title: World Series Game 1: JT Realmuto’s Homer Gives Phillies 10th Inning Win
description: Houston got off to an early 5-0 lead but watched it evaporate. Realmuto tied the game with a double in the fifth and put his team ahead to stay with a homer in the 10th.
dc:creator: James Wagner
media:credit: Annie Mulligan for The New York Times
media:description: J.T. Realmuto went 2 for 4 with a home run and three R.B.I. in Philadelphia’s win over Houston in Game 1 of the World Series.
